9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 965, L.D. 1473, “An Act to Require
10 Utilities to Monitor Meters for Natural Gas Leaks”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Require Gas Utilities to Assess for Natural Gas Leaks and to Require
13 Reporting of Gas Leak Information'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
15 following:
16 'Sec. 1. 35-A MRSA §4713 is enacted to read:
17 §4713. Assessment and report of natural gas leaks
18 1. Gas utilities to assess for natural gas leaks. A gas utility shall assess its natural
19 gas system for natural gas leaks, including every natural gas main and meter under its
20 jurisdiction, as frequently as may be required by the commission by rule, but no less
21 frequently than every 3 years.
22 2. Gas utility; reporting. Each gas utility shall provide reports to the commission at a
23 frequency as established by the commission by rule regarding the number of natural gas
24 leaks identified by the gas utility and the actions taken by the gas utility to address the
25 natural gas leaks. The reports must protect individually identifiable customer information
26 by omitting customer names and addresses, except that the reports must include street
27 location information for the identified natural gas leaks. The commission shall post the
28 reports received from gas utilities in accordance with this subsection on the commission's
29 publicly accessible website.
30 3. Commission; reporting. No later than April 1, 2026 and annually thereafter, the
31 commission shall provide a report to the joint standing committee of the Legislature having
32 jurisdiction over utility matters. The report must list each gas utility providing service in
33 the State and the number of natural gas leaks identified by the gas utility in the prior
34 calendar year by street location and must describe any action taken by the gas utility to
35 address the natural gas leaks. The report must protect individually identifiable customer
