COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 965, L.D. 1473
316 information by omitting customer names and addresses. The commission shall post the
327 reports required by this subsection on the commission's publicly accessible website.
3 4. Compliance. The commission shall periodically assess gas utility compliance with
4 the requirements of subsections 1 and 2 at a frequency determined by the commission.
5 5. Rules. The commission may adopt rules to carry out the purposes of this section.
6 Rules adopted pursuant to this subsection are routine technical rules as defined in Title 5,
7 chapter 375, subchapter 2-A.'
8 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
9 number to read consecutively.
10 SUMMARY
1111 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. It requires a gas utility to assess
1122 its natural gas system, including every natural gas main and meter under its jurisdiction, as
1133 frequently as may be required by the Public Utilities Commission by rule, but no less
1144 frequently than every 3 years. It requires gas utilities to provide reports to the commission
1155 at a frequency as established by the commission by rule, regarding the number of natural
1166 gas leaks identified by the gas utility, the street location for the natural gas leaks and the
1177 actions taken by the gas utility to address the natural gas leaks. It also requires the
1188 commission to file an annual report to the joint standing committee of the Legislature
1199 having jurisdiction over utility matters regarding natural gas leaks reported by gas utilities
2200 and to include natural gas leak reports on its publicly accessible website. The commission
2211 is required to periodically assess gas utility compliance with the assessment and reporting
2222 requirements.
